

=Description=

John Gilmore:

"The Flying Laptop project in Stuttgart is focused mainly on the verification of the satellite’s capabilities and scientific earth surveillance. Another group of students created Lambdasat which is going to be used to monitor Greek ships in pirate infested waters, but the most interesting satellite project of all is from another artist, Sun Ho-jun, who built a mini satellite for $500 using spare parts he found around town."
(http://bezdomny.org/?p=492)


